resources.string: There are no tests available at this time. Your schedule will be determined at your baseline visit.

The following section will ask you questions in regards to your sleep and wake behaviour on work- and work-free days. Please estimate an average of your \"normal\" sleep behaviour over the past 6 weeks when you were able to follow your usual routines.
I have been a shift- or night-worker in the past three months.
Please answer all of the following questions even if you do not work or work 7 days/week. Please don\'t forget to indicate AM or PM.
I normally fall asleep at (this is NOT when you get to bed):
I normally wake up at (this is NOT when you get out of bed):
On work-free days when I don\'t use an alarm clock...
Who is with you right now?
Which of these best describes your overall mood right now?
Which of these best describes how you feel right now?
In the past 5 minutes...what were you MOSTLY doing?

In this test, you will see a 5 x 5 grid. 

There will be three items placed in that grid. 

Try to remember where the items are located.
You will then do a different task where you will touch all the letter \'F\'s that you find as quickly as you can.
Then, you\'ll be shown a blank grid. Tap the boxes where that items were located previously. Press Start to begin.
Try to remember the location of the items!
Please sign your initials on the line below to verify your identity.
By signing my initials on the line below, I attest that I completed these tests.
Were you interrupted or did you have to stop while taking any of these tests?
You finished this test, are you ready for the next one?
You will now start the test. You will see an item and two prices. \nPlease select the price that matches the item you studied.

When do you usually wake up?
When do you usually go to bed?
You will need about five minutes to complete everything, maybe less. You will be asked a few questions and then you will complete three quick tests. Press Next to begin.
Please set the next start date for the participant.

You will see three pairs of symbols at the top of the screen and two pairs at the bottom. 

As quickly as you can, tap the pair at the bottom of the screen that matches one of the pairs at the top.
 
Press Start to begin.
Which pair below matches one of the pairs on the top?
You finished this test, ready for the next one?

You will now complete three quick tests. 

You cannot pause this test once it has been started.
 
Press Next to begin.
What time did you get in bed last night?
How long did it take you to fall asleep?
How many times did you wake up for 5 minutes or longer?
What time did you wake up in the morning?
What time did you get out of bed?
How would you rate the quality of your sleep?
There are no tests available at this time. \nYou will be notified when it is time to start.
I NEED TO ADJUST MY START DATE
It’s time to take a quick test!
You\'ve missed your tests. If you\'re unable \nto finish this week, please contact your site \ncoordinator.
Please confirm your next test date.
Do you plan to upgrade your phone in the next 3 months?
Your next test will begin on {DATE} .
Please confirm or adjust the start date.

In this task, we’ll show you some shopping items and prices. 

Please decide if the displayed price is a "good bargain" for that item.
 
The pair will only remain on the screen for a short time so please make your decision quickly and pay careful attention.

After you see 10 pairs of shopping items and prices, you will be asked to match the correct price with each item so try to remember the prices.

Press Start to begin.
Your next test will be on {DATE}.
